Author: jcsxx
Text: You are not at the point of no return. Tbh though, once the feeling left me it did not come back until I started eating like a normal person for several weeks. Your body and mind will recalibrate when you are physically healthy enough. I’m so sorry you’re going through this. I still feel that disassociation sometimes and mourn the loss of my excitement related to food. It feels not only  like a genuine loss but like something was stolen from you. But it will come back with time and healing

Author: aphterglow
Text: Does it physically or mentally feel unnatural? Either way in my experience it didn’t last.
